---
const pageTitle = "AI-Forward QA System";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --bg: #0b0e14;
        --panel: #121827;
        --text: #e6e9ef;
        --muted: #aab2c5;
        --link: #7aa2ff;
        --border: #24304d;
        --bad: #ff7b72;
        --warn: #f0b429;
        --good: #3ddc97;
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, Arial;
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--text);
      }

      a {
        color: var(--link);
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
      }

      .wrap {
        max-width: 1060px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 22px 18px 54px;
      }

      .pill {
        display: inline-block;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
        padding: 8px 12px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        color: var(--text);
      }

      .card {
        background: var(--panel);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 16px;
        padding: 20px;
        margin-top: 16px;
      }

      .grid {
        display: grid;
        gap: 16px;
      }

      .grid2 {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 38px;
        line-height: 1.1;
        margin: 8px 0 12px;
      }

      .lead,
      p,
      li {
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.6;
      }

      h2 {
        margin: 0 0 10px;
        font-size: 24px;
      }

      h3 {
        margin: 0 0 8px;
        font-size: 18px;
      }

      ul,
      ol {
        margin: 8px 0 0 18px;
      }

      .cta {
        display: flex;
        gap: 12px;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        margin-top: 16px;
      }

      .trust-low {
        color: var(--bad);
      }

      .trust-med {
        color: var(--warn);
      }

      .trust-high {
        color: var(--good);
      }

      footer {
        margin-top: 28px;
        padding-top: 16px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        color: var(--muted);
      }

      @media (max-width: 900px) {
        .grid2 {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        h1 {
          font-size: 32px;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="wrap">
      <a class="pill" href="/offerings/">← Back to offering paths</a>

      <h1>AI-Forward QA System</h1>

      <p class="lead">
        Move fast without losing control. AI generates plans, page objects, and specs
        quickly, but nothing matters until it survives deterministic execution, artifact
        capture, triage, and release control.
      </p>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>What this path is</h2>
        <p>
          This is the accelerated path for teams already embracing AI-generated tests.
          Generation is not the value by itself. The value is a validation layer strong
          enough to make the output safe.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid2">
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Walkthrough structure</h2>
          <ol>
            <li>AI generation of plans, locators, and tests</li>
            <li>Validation pass on structure and assumptions</li>
            <li>Deterministic execution layer</li>
            <li>Structured failure artifacts and classification</li>
            <li>Release decision through GO / WARN / BLOCK</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h2>What you get</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Validated AI-generated assets</li>
            <li>Artifact-first failure outputs</li>
            <li>triage-report.json</li>
            <li>release-gate.json</li>
            <li>Repeatable execution pipeline</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>Trust-based entry points</h2>

        <div class="grid grid2">
          <div>
            <h3 class="trust-low">Low trust</h3>
            <p>AI-forward on a low-trust system will fail. This path is not the starting point.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Run anti-pattern validation first</li>
              <li>Stabilize with Sprint 3–5</li>
              <li>Adopt AI-forward only after trust improves</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="trust-med">Medium trust</h3>
            <p>Acceleration becomes possible if the validation layer is added immediately.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Sprint 14 — Artifact Contract</li>
              <li>Sprint 15 — CI Failure Triage Agent</li>
              <li>Sprint 17 — Release Gate Agent</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="trust-high" style="margin-top: 16px;">High trust</h3>
            <p>This is where the AI-forward path actually works well.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Sprint 9.5 — URL-to-Test-Plan Agent</li>
              <li>Sprint 14–17 — Full validation and decision layer</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>Who this is for</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Teams already generating tests with AI</li>
          <li>Teams under delivery pressure</li>
          <li>Teams that need speed and safety at the same time</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="cta">
          <a
            class="pill"
            href="mailto:qaalignllc@gmail.com?subject=AI-Forward%20QA%20System"
          >
            Talk through the AI-forward path
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <footer>QA Test Lab — AI-Forward QA System</footer>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>